N2  - This study used a structural equation model to identify the predictors of support for a college affirmative action policy for Asian Americans. A sample of 291 non-Asian students at a midsize public university with a large Asian American population completed an online survey. Attitudes toward Asian Americans were somewhat negative and support for affirmative action was modest. Results indicated that principled policy attitudes and subjective norms were the strongest predictors of support; non-prejudicial attitudes and self-interest did not predict support. Previous contact was an antecedent variable which indirectly predicted support mediated by subjective norms. Ethnicity and gender did not directly or indirectly predict support. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
