N2  - After working with many minority communities in California, the author is very prejudiced against translating nutrition education materials designed for the mainstream population into the languages of minority populations. It can be insulting when there is no attempt to insure the content is culturally appropriate and relevant. Instead of asking a bilingual person to translate word for word, ask the person to rewrite the pamphlet by focusing on the advice you are attempting to share with the target population. Then have another translator back-translate the text into English to see if it communicates the advice correctly. If it doesn't, explain the problems and have it rewritten again in the native language.. (PsycInfo Database Record (c) 2021 APA, all rights reserved)
